AMR sphere example (generic text format)
========================================

Files
-----
  sphere_amr.dat          Sample AMR leaf-cell data (112 cells, 100 kpc box)
  sphere_amr_tau4.in      Point source, tau=1e4, no peel-off
  sphere_amr_tau4_peel.in Point source, tau=1e4, with peel-off + Jin output
  run.sh                  Convenience run script

Data file format (sphere_amr.dat)
----------------------------------
Header (1 line):
  nleaf  boxlen_kpc

One line per leaf cell:
  x[kpc]  y[kpc]  z[kpc]  level  nH[cm^-3]  T[K]  vx[km/s]  vy[km/s]  vz[km/s]

  x, y, z   : leaf-cell centre in kpc (origin at box corner, i.e., 0 .. boxlen_kpc)
  level      : AMR refinement level (1 = root)
  nH         : total hydrogen number density [cm^-3]
  T          : gas temperature [K]
  vx/vy/vz   : bulk velocity [km/s]

Neutral fraction:
  By default (par%use_cie_condition = .false.) all hydrogen is assumed neutral.
  Set par%use_cie_condition = .true. to estimate nHI/nH from CIE.

Key AMR parameters
------------------
  par%use_amr_grid = .true.
  par%amr_type     = 'generic'       ! or 'ramses'
  par%amr_file     = 'sphere_amr.dat'

Grid structure in this example
------------------------------
  Level 2 cells (25 kpc) fill the outer volume (r > 30 kpc from box centre).
  Level 3 cells (12.5 kpc) fill the inner sphere (r < 30 kpc).
  Density profile: nH(r) = nH0 * exp(-r^2 / 2*(30 kpc)^2)
  Temperature: uniform 10^4 K, static gas (v=0).

Running
-------
  cd examples/amr_sphere_generic
  mpirun -np 4 ../../LaRT.x sphere_amr_tau4.in

Output files
------------
  sphere_amr_tau4.fits.gz        Emergent spectrum / surface brightness map
  sphere_amr_tau4_peel.fits.gz   Peel-off observer image (if save_peeloff=.true.)
